# Invobolt — environment variables
#
# Instant mode (v0.1, this repo) needs NO environment variables at all:
# the generator runs entirely in the browser.
#
# The variables below configure the OPTIONAL workspace mode (v0.2). They are
# read only when WORKSPACE_ENABLED=true; leave it unset and the build ignores
# them entirely.

# --- Workspace mode (v0.2, opt-in) ---
# Off by default: leave WORKSPACE_ENABLED unset and the app is exactly the
# instant-mode-only build (no accounts, no database, no env vars needed).
# Set it to "true" AND provide DATABASE_URL to mount the /app workspace.
# WORKSPACE_ENABLED=true

# Postgres connection string (Neon is the documented default; any Postgres works).
# Apply the app schema (clients, invoices) with `npm run db:migrate`.
# DATABASE_URL=

# Authentication is handled by Neon Auth (Managed Better Auth). Enable Neon Auth
# on your Neon project, then set the values it gives you. Neon Auth manages its
# own user tables in the `neon_auth` schema and sends magic-link emails itself —
# no separate email provider is needed for sign-in.
#
# Base URL of your Neon Auth instance.
# NEON_AUTH_BASE_URL=https://your-project.neon.tech
# Secret for signing session cookies — must be at least 32 chars.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
# NEON_AUTH_COOKIE_SECRET=

# Email delivery for sending invoices (planned v0.3, optional).
# EMAIL_FROM=
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# --- Stripe import (planned v0.3, always optional) ---
# Read-only restricted key used to import customers & products.
# STRIPE_RESTRICTED_KEY=
